<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN292">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>vēntaṟ kēntiya tīntaṇ ṇaṟavam</l>
<l>yāntaṉak kuṟumuṟai vaḷāva vilakki</l>
<l>vāyvāḷ paṟṟi niṉṟaṉa ṉeṉṟu</l>
<l>ciṉava lōmpumiṉ ciṟupul lāḷa</l>
<l>rīṇṭē pōla vēṇṭuva ṉāyi</l>
<l>ṉeṉmuṟai varuka veṉṉāṉ kammeṉa</l>
<l>veḻutaru perumpaṭai vilakki</l>
<l>yāṇṭu niṟku māṇtakai yaṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“The sweet cool licquor held out to the king,</l>
<l>refusing [it] when we diluted [it] the turn [it] fell on him</l>
<l>he stood, gripping [his] excellent sword,” </l>
<l>beware of being angry [at this]. “If he, like the small, low</l>
<l>men here wants [it], </l>
<l>let my turn come,” he did not say so,</l>
<l>the one fit for glory who stands everywhere,</l>
<l>blocking the big army that rose noisily.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
